## Comparative Summary of Arguments

| Aspect                    | Arguments For Capital Punishment                                     | Arguments Against Capital Punishment                                |
|---------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Justice**               | Punishment fits the crime (retributivism)                          | Retribution equates to revenge; morally flawed                     |
| **Deterrence**            | Reduces crime rates; deters potential offenders                    | No conclusive evidence of deterrence; likelihood of being caught matters more |
| **Risk of Error**         | System can be improved; errors are ancillary issues                | Irreversible execution of innocent people is unacceptable          |
| **Human Rights**          | Murderers forfeit right to life                                    | Right to life is inalienable; state should not take life           |
| **Cost**                  | Death penalty can be cost-effective                               | Legal processes make it more expensive than life imprisonment      |
| **Societal Impact**       | Provides closure to victims’ families; removes dangerous criminals | Brutalizes society; increases violence; perpetuates injustice      |
| **Ethical Execution**     | Modern methods are humane                                         | Methods may cause suffering; medical ethics violated               |
| **Fairness**              | Legal safeguards exist                                            | Disproportionate impact on minorities and poor                     |

